    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. AMASH:H.J. Res. 54.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:This resolution is enacted pursuant to the powers conferredby the United States Constitution upon Congress by Article V.which provides that ``The Congress, whenever two thirds ofboth Houses shall deem it necessary, shall propose Amendmentsto this Constitution .  .  . which shall be valid to allIntents and Purposes, as Part of this Constitution, whenratified by the Legislatures of three fourths of the severalStates .  .  .''____________________[Page H3310]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
